#Time series analysis
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
df=pd.read_csv('retail_sales_dataset.csv')

df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])
df.set_index('Date', inplace=True)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(df.index, df['Total Amount'])
plt.title('Sales Over Time')
plt.xlabel('date')
plt.ylabel('Total Amount')
plt.show()

#Customer and product analysis and purchasing behaviour
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import datetime as dt
df=pd.read_csv('retail_sales_dataset.csv')
df['AgeRange'] = pd.cut(df['Age'], bins=[0, 25, 40, 60, float('inf')],
                                labels=['<25', '25-40', '40-60', '60+'])


avg_purchase_by_age = df.groupby('AgeRange')['Price per Unit'].mean()
print(avg_purchase_by_age)
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])
today_date = pd.to_datetime('2024-08-06') 
df['Date'] = (today_date - df['Date'])

avg_recency_by_segment = df.groupby('Quantity')['Date'].mean()
print(avg_recency_by_segment)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.bar(avg_purchase_by_age.index, avg_purchase_by_age.values)
plt.xlabel('Age Range')
plt.ylabel('Average Purchase Amount')
plt.title('Average Purchase Amount by Age Range')
plt.show()

In [43]:
#visulaization
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
df=pd.read_csv('retail_sales_dataset.csv')

#bar plot
category_sales = df.groupby('Product Category')['Total Amount'].sum()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(category_sales.index, category_sales.values)
plt.xlabel('Product Category')
plt.ylabel('Total Sales Amount')
plt.title('Sales by Product Category')
plt.show()

#line plot
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])
monthly_sales = df.resample('M', on='Date')['Total Amount'].sum()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(monthly_sales.index, monthly_sales.values, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Monthly Sales Amount')
plt.title('Monthly Sales Trends')
plt.show()

#Heatmap
numerical_features = ['Total Amount', 'Quantity', 'Price per Unit']
corr_matrix = df[numerical_features].corr()

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', square=True)
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
df=pd.read_csv("menu.csv")
df

#Data Cleaning
print(df.dropna(inplace=True))
print(df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True))

#Description Statistics
mean= df['Calories'].mean()
median = df['Calories'].median()
mode = df['Calories'].mode().iloc[0]
std = df['Calories'].std()

print(f"MEAN : {mean}")
print(f"MEDIAN : {median}")
print(f"MODE : {mode}")
print(f"STANDARD DEVIATION : {std}")

#bar plot
category_sales = df.groupby('Category')['Total Fat (% Daily Value)'].sum()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(category_sales.index, category_sales.values)
plt.xlabel('Category')
plt.ylabel('Total Fat (% Daily Value)')
plt.title('Total fat by Product Category')
plt.show()


#Heatmap
numerical_features = ['Trans Fat', 'Total Fat', 'Calories']
corr_matrix = df[numerical_features].corr()

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', square=True)
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')
plt.show()
